# 🤖 SDLC Copilot — File Summarizer

> Fetch any file from a GitHub repo and get an AI-powered summary — built with **GitHub Copilot SDK**, **Next.js**, **Express**, and **Turborepo**.

## Architecture

```
sdlc-copilot/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/        ← Next.js 15 frontend (port 3000)
│   └── server/     ← Express API + Copilot SDK (port 4000)
├── packages/
│   └── shared/     ← Shared TypeScript types
├── turbo.json
└── package.json
```

**Flow:**
1. User enters **owner / repo / file path** in the UI
2. Frontend streams a request to the Express server via SSE
3. Server creates a Copilot SDK session with the **GitHub MCP server**
4. Copilot uses GitHub MCP tools to fetch the file, then summarizes it
5. Summary streams back to the UI in real-time (Markdown rendered)

## Prerequisites

| Requirement | Version |
|---|---|
| **Node.js** | 18+ |
| **GitHub Copilot CLI** | latest |
| **npm** | 10+ |

### Install & authenticate Copilot CLI

```bash
npm install -g @github/copilot-cli
copilot auth login
copilot --version   # verify
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Clone / navigate to the project
cd sdlc-copilot

# 2. Copy env file and customise if needed
cp .env.example .env

# 3. Install all dependencies (workspaces + turbo)
npm install

# 4. Start both apps in dev mode
npm run dev
```

This runs:
- **Web UI** → http://localhost:3000
- **API Server** → http://localhost:4000

## Configuration (.env)

| Variable | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
